                  </Label>
                  <Text layoutX="30.0" layoutY="178.0" strokeType="OUTSIDE" strokeWidth="0.0" text="Electricity is the flow of electric charge, primarily through electrons in a conductor. It is a fundamental part of modern life, powering our homes, devices, and industries. The basic quantities involved in electricity are voltage (V), current (I), and resistance (R). Voltage is the electric potential difference that drives charges through a circuit, current is the rate of charge flow, and resistance opposes this flow. These are related by Ohmâ€™s Law: V = IR." textAlignment="JUSTIFY" wrappingWidth="727.7760620117188">
