                        <Font name="Segoe UI" size="16.0" />
                     </font>
                  </Text>
                  <Text layoutX="30.0" layoutY="297.0" strokeType="OUTSIDE" strokeWidth="0.0" text="In a simple electric circuit, components like batteries, resistors, and light bulbs are connected using conductors (wires). Circuits can be arranged in series or parallel, each with different rules for how current and voltage behave. Understanding how to analyze circuits allows students to design and troubleshoot electrical systems, from flashlights to complex electronic devices." textAlignment="JUSTIFY" wrappingWidth="727.7760620117188">
