                        <Font name="Segoe UI" size="16.0" />
                     </font>
                  </Text>
                  <Label layoutX="30.0" layoutY="374.0" prefHeight="53.0" prefWidth="686.0" text="Magnetism and Electromagnetism">
                     <font>
                        <Font name="Segoe UI Semibold" size="25.0" />
                     </font>
                  </Label>
                  <Text layoutX="30.0" layoutY="446.0" strokeType="OUTSIDE" strokeWidth="0.0" text="Magnetism arises from moving electric charges and is most commonly observed in materials like iron that can become magnetized. Magnetic fields are invisible regions around magnets where magnetic forces are exerted. These fields have both direction and strength, and their patterns can be visualized using iron filings or simulated digitally." textAlignment="JUSTIFY" wrappingWidth="727.7760620117188">
                     <font>
                        <Font name="Segoe UI" size="16.0" />
                     </font>
                  </Text>
                  <Text layoutX="30.0" layoutY="540.0" strokeType="OUTSIDE" strokeWidth="0.0" text="The combination of electricity and magnetism is known as electromagnetism. Electromagnets work on the idea that a magnetic field is created when current passes through a wire. On the other hand, Faraday's Law of Electromagnetic Induction demonstrates that a fluctuating magnetic field can cause current to flow through a wire. Electric generators, transformers, and numerous contemporary technologies, like wireless charging and MRI equipment, are all based on this idea." textAlignment="JUSTIFY" wrappingWidth="727.7760620117188">
                     <font>
                        <Font name="Segoe UI" size="16.0" />
                     </font>
                  </Text>
                  <Label layoutX="30.0" layoutY="638.0" prefHeight="53.0" prefWidth="686.0" text="Waves and Sound">
