                        <Font name="Segoe UI Semibold" size="25.0" />
                     </font>
                  </Label>
                  <Text layoutX="30.0" layoutY="707.0" strokeType="OUTSIDE" strokeWidth="0.0" text="Waves are repeating disturbances that transfer energy without transferring matter. Mechanical waves, like sound, require a medium to travel through, while electromagnetic waves (like light) do not. Key properties of waves include wavelength, frequency, amplitude, and speed. These properties determine how a wave behaves and interacts with its surroundings." textAlignment="JUSTIFY" wrappingWidth="727.7760620117188">
                     <font>
                        <Font name="Segoe UI" size="16.0" />
                     </font>
                  </Text>
                  <Text layoutX="30.0" layoutY="801.0" strokeType="OUTSIDE" strokeWidth="0.0" text="Sound is a longitudinal wave that travels through solids, liquids, and gases. Its pitch depends on frequency, and its loudness relates to amplitude. Phenomena such as reflection, interference, resonance, and Doppler effect all arise from wave behavior. Understanding waves is crucial not only in music and acoustics but also in medical imaging, communication systems, and earthquake detection." textAlignment="JUSTIFY" wrappingWidth="727.7760620117188">
                     <font>
                        <Font name="Segoe UI" size="16.0" />
                     </font>
                  </Text>
                  <Label layoutX="30.0" layoutY="878.0" prefHeight="53.0" prefWidth="686.0" text="Light and Optics">
