                     </font>
                  </Label>
                  <Text layoutX="30.0" layoutY="947.0" strokeType="OUTSIDE" strokeWidth="0.0" text="Light behaves both as a wave and as a particle, a dual nature explored more in modern physics. As a wave, light can reflect, refract, diffract, and interfere. When light travels from one medium to another (like air to water), its speed changes, causing it to bend, this then produces refraction. This principle is used in lenses and optical instruments like cameras, microscopes, and eyeglasses." textAlignment="JUSTIFY" wrappingWidth="727.7760620117188">
                     <font>
                        <Font name="Segoe UI" size="16.0" />
                     </font>
                  </Text>
                  <Text layoutX="30.0" layoutY="1041.0" strokeType="OUTSIDE" strokeWidth="0.0" text="Mirrors reflect light based on the angle of incidence and reflection, while lenses refract light to focus or spread out beams. Optics, the study of light behavior, is essential in designing everything from telescopes to fiber-optic networks. By mastering the principles of light and optics, students can better understand the science behind vision, photography, lasers, and even holograms." textAlignment="JUSTIFY" wrappingWidth="727.7760620117188">
